This paper deals with access control policies and data mining, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper focuses on attribute-based access control (ABAC) and its potential to improve security. The second likely category is cs.DB (Databases), as the paper uses operation logs and attribute data to mine ABAC policies. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper presents an algorithm for mining ABAC policies. The fourth likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering), as ABAC policies are an important aspect of software security. The fifth likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper uses data mining techniques to extract ABAC policies from logs and attribute data.
